-- Djokovic Defeats Ferrer to Complete Semifinals Lineup at Australian Open
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-01-25T11:28:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-25/djokovic-defeats-ferrer-to-complete-semifinals-lineup-at-australian-open.html
Top-rankedNovak Djokovic beat  David Ferrer  6-4, 7-6 (7-4), 6-1 to complete the Australian Open
semifinals lineup, which will feature the top four men.  Defending champion Djokovic of Serbia will face Andy Murray
in two days for a place in the Jan. 29 title match at Melbourne
Park. The fourth-seeded Briton earlier beat Kei Nishikori of
Japan in straight sets.  No. 2 seed Rafael Nadal of Spain and third-seeded  Roger Federer  of Switzerland will play their semifinal tomorrow.  Women’s No. 4 seed Maria Sharapova beat Ekaterina Makarova
to set up a rematch of the 2011 Wimbledon final against second-
seeded Petra Kvitova, who defeated the unseeded Sara Errani.
Both women’s semifinals are scheduled for tomorrow, with the
championship match on Jan. 28.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
